  <title>Gio.SocketMsgFlags</title>
  <p>Flags used in <link xref="Gio.Socket.receive_message"/> and <link xref="Gio.Socket.send_message"/>.
The flags listed in the enum are some commonly available flags, but the
values used for them are the same as on the platform, and any other flags
are passed in/out as is. So to use a platform specific flag, just include
the right system header and pass in the flag.</p>
  <p>Since 2.22</p>
<terms>
<item>
<title><code>SocketMsgFlags.NONE</code></title>
  <p>No flags.</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>SocketMsgFlags.OOB</code></title>
  <p>Request to send/receive out of band data.</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>SocketMsgFlags.PEEK</code></title>
  <p>Read data from the socket without removing it from
    the queue.</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>SocketMsgFlags.DONTROUTE</code></title>
  <p>Don't use a gateway to send out the packet,
    only send to hosts on directly connected networks.</p>
</item>
